    <p>Will things re­turn to nor­mal this year or will it be Pan­demic: Year Two?</p>
    <p>Last year, Covid-19 caused ma­jor films to push release dates to this year, mainly be­cause of lock­downs af­fect­ing cin­ema pa­tron­age in the United States.</p>
    <p>But the Amer­i­can sit­u­a­tion should mat­ter less this year as ma­jor Hol­ly­wood stu­dios have de­cided to cut their risks.</p>
    <p>This year, on­line re­leases on plat­forms such as Dis­ney+ and HBO Max will be­come the backup op­tion or maybe even the first.</p>
    <p>This means that in Sin­ga­pore, the ma­jor films listed here are likely to open as planned in cin­e­mas.</p>
    <p>Here are the top movies to catch in the year ahead.</p>

